view.name: EMS - Quarterly Clinical Measures - Trauma Alert
view.description: This table contains data describing ATCEMS management of Trauma Alert patients.  In this setting, “Trauma Alert” refers to injured patients who meet Physiological or Anatomical criteria for transport to a Trauma Center per City of Austin/Travis County EMS System Clinical Operating Guidelines.

approvals.message: The `strict_permissions` flag must be on to enable internal approvals.

columns.name: Fiscal Quarter Key
columns.description: Row identifier – numeric representation of fiscal quarter in <yyyyqq> format.

columns.name: Fiscal Quarter
columns.description: Year and fiscal quarter for record in <yyyy-qq> format (e.g. 2014-Q1).

columns.name: Fiscal Quarter Start Date
columns.description: First day of fiscal quarter, presented in <mmm yyyy> format.

columns.name: Fiscal Quarter End Date
columns.description: Last day of fiscal quarter, presented in <mmm yyyy> format.

columns.name: Count - Trauma Alert Scene Interval Compliance
columns.description: Count of Trauma Alert patients with a scene interval less than 15 minutes.  Scene interval starts when the first ATCEMS personnel arrive on scene, and ends when ATCEMS personnel depart the scene.

columns.name: Percent – Trauma Alert Scene Interval Compliance
columns.description: Percent of Trauma Alert patients with a scene interval less than 15 minutes.

columns.name: Trauma Alert Scene Interval Compliance Target
columns.description: Target performance level for compliance with scene time goal for Trauma Alert patients.

columns.name: Count - Trauma Center Transports
columns.description: Count of Trauma Alert patients who are transported to a system approved Trauma Center.

columns.name: Percent - Trauma Center Transports
columns.description: Percent of Trauma Alert patients who are transported to a system approved Trauma Center.

columns.name: Trauma Center Transport Compliance Target
columns.description: Target specialty center transport rate for Trauma Alert patients.

columns.name: Average Call to Door Interval (Minutes)
columns.description: Average interval between first 911 call and arrival at the receiving facility for Trauma Alert patients, measured in decimal minutes (e.g. 37.7 minutes).

columns.name: Call to Door Interval Target
columns.description: Target for Average Call to Door Interval.
